cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR 

This paper involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques to compare two multimodal resources that consist of diagrams which describe topics in elementary school natural sciences. The paper evaluates how effectively crowd-sourced and expert-annotated graphs can represent the multimodal structure of diagrams for representation learning using various graph neural networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper involves image analysis and computer vision techniques, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also involves AI techniques, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category. Finally, since the paper involves information retrieval techniques to classify diagrams and their parts, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible sub-category.
